  "prompt": "How much does an average subway franchise make per year?",
  "response": "The earnings of an average Subway franchise can vary significantly based on factors such as location, management, and local market conditions. However, as of my last update, the average annual gross sales for a Subway franchise typically ranged from around $300,000 to $500,000. \n\nIt's important to note that these figures represent gross sales, not net profit. After accounting for expenses such as rent, payroll, food costs, and franchise fees, the net profit for franchise owners can vary widely. Some franchisees may earn a few thousand dollars, while others might generate a more substantial income depending on their operating efficiency and market conditions.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's advisable to consult Subway's Franchise Disclosure Document (FDD) or speak directly with current franchise owners.",
